        }
      ]
    },
    "Complications": {
      "text": "Theoretical risk of\npneumothorax\nwith hold-up sign\nNo high-quality evidence to suggest bougie use leads to increased mechanical complications of intubation\n[6]\nBEAM trial showed no difference in incidence of airway trauma between bougie and stylet groups",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "pneumothorax",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Pneumothorax"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Procedure": {
      "text": "Obtain view with Mac blade laryngoscope (\ndirect\nor \"standard-geometry\"\nvideo\n)\nPass bougie - confirm with tracheal clicks and/or hold up sign\nHave assistant \"railroad\" tube over bougie\nAlternatively can use preloaded ETT over bougie for single-operator using \"kiwi\" grip",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "direct",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Direct_laryngoscopy"
        },
        {
          "text": "video",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Video_Laryngoscopy"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Pitfalls": {
      "text": "Removing laryngoscope before railroading ETT can cause difficulty in passing the tube\nIf resistance is met, retract tube 1-2 cm and rotate 90° CCW, then advance tube",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
